			<ns0:name>s...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108394971971967673680/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The work-in-progress fragmentation of SRPC messages has two end-to-end tests.  One (run_srpc_fragment_test) tests turning the fragment size down to one byte to check that messages are correctly fragmented and reassembled.  The other (run_srpc_huge_test) tests that passing large amounts of data results in correct fragmentation.

It would be better to be able to test the whole message passing and fragmentation layer independently of SRPC, both in trusted and untrusted code.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-10-19T16:14:44.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-13T15:54:51.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Duplicate</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
